external_knowledge:
- "Top players" are those ranked 1-3 within their positions based on jersey numbers;
- "Teams that have played more than 5 games" refers to teams with a total game count greater than 5;
- "Order of their team's total wins" means the players are listed with teams having the highest number of wins first.

- "Top-performing player" refers to the player with the highest number of wins within their team;
- "User with the ID of 1" refers to a specific user in the system who has access to multiple teams;
- "Star players" are those who rank first in their team based on the number of wins;
- "Privilege to witness" implies the user has access to the team data.

- "Guard," "Forward," and "Center" refer to specific positions in basketball;
- "Win" and "Loss" are outcomes of games;
- "Coach" and "Analyst" are roles within the team's management.

- "shone in games more crowded than the usual gathering" refers to games where the attendance is higher than the average attendance for that team;
- "usual gathering" refers to the average attendance for a team;
- "witness their brilliance" refers to the number of people present at the game.

- "Senior" refers to a player who is in their final year of college;
- "Forward" is a position in basketball;
- "Highest jersey number" implies the largest number assigned to a player within their team.

- 'significant number of players' refers to more than 5 players;
- 'significant number of games' refers to more than 10 games;
- Player heights are assumed to be in feet and inches, formatted as 'X'Y" (e.g., 6'2").

- "stands tallest" refers to the team with the highest win-loss ratio;
- "champion among its peers" refers to the team with the best performance in the league;
- "ratio of its victories to its defeats" refers to the win-loss ratio.

- "battles fought" refers to the total number of games played by each team;
- "prowess" refers to the average score of the games;
- "warriors" refers to the active users in the team;
- "standing tall" implies the teams are ranked by the total number of games played and then by average score.

- "tasted victory" refers to having at least one win;
- "fields a guard" refers to having at least one player in the guard position;
- "closely watched by the keen eyes of analysts" refers to being associated with at least one user with the role of analyst;
- "beacon of success" implies the team is popular among analysts, as indicated by the highest number of distinct analysts.
